The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks and skip-gram models for recommendation systems, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the mapping of courses and traversals across them, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these techniques for content tagging (cs.CL) and the development of a user interface (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of the system at a university, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
